/**
 * PLAYER QUESTIONS DATA FILE (Select a Legend)
 * =============================================
 * Authored questions per player; each World Cup tile is exactly 10 questions about that tournament (`getPlayerLevelChunkSize`).
 * Tier minimums use World Cup finals years they actually played (`getPlayerWorldCupYearsSorted`); squad-only / zero-minute years are listed in `playerWorldCupSquadOnlyYears` or omitted from `playerWorldCupYears`. Thin mode if the pool cannot fill enough levels.
 * If the pool cannot meet the tier minimum,
 * the player is “thin”: one flat run with every unique question (`getPlayerFlatQuizQuestions`).
 * Pools are normalized to 10/20/30/40/50 questions so level mode always lines up on tens.
 * `dedupeLegendPlayerQuestions()` drops exact repeats and near-paraphrases.
 * Off-topic noise is stripped in `filterOffTopicPlayerQuestions`. Under 10 usable → thin flat quiz.
 * Short pools may merge extras from `buildExtraQuestions` (templates are empty; thin pools rely on authored facts).
 * `applyMatchLogPolicyToPool` strips career/total prompts, assigns `eventYear`, strips redundant “In/At the [YEAR] World Cup…” openers when present, and blocks cross-year leaks.
 * Level mode: `getPlayerQuestionsByLevel` picks prompts by `eventYear` / stem year so each level matches
 * `getPlayerWorldCupYearForLevel` (same year as the host flag on the level card). Neutral career-wide prompts are not used to pad levels.
 */

